President Barack Obama has announced his intention to nominate Myles Watts as a Member of the Board of Directors for the Federal Agricultural Mortgage Corporation. Watts is currently a professor in the Department of Agricultural Economics and Economics at Montana State University. He has been with the university since 1978, serving as Department Head for 17 years. His responsibilities include teaching, research, and outreach education. Watts has also held editorial roles for the Journal of Agricultural and Resource Economics and has received various honors and awards from professional associations. He was raised in southeastern Montana on a cattle and wheat ranch that is still owned and operated by his family.